</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> I am a level 19 dwarven paladin I am using a 19/40 2HS weapon.  My 2HS skill is listed as &quot;average&quot; as I spent my lower levels using 1HS and bashing with my shield.  Occasionally, I hit for 29 but often I just miss entirely.<br>
<br>
Looking for advice.  Will my damage output increase significantly when I get double attack at 20?  Will I start hitting for more consistently?  Should I drop my remaining training points into double attack when I reach 20 or put more into 2HS?<br>
<br>
Please don't suggest that I just go out and buy a much better weapon - I am anything but rich.  I am just looking for insight into the transition of a paladin into medium levels.   I don't have Luclin so looting a Strength of Grodan is not an option.<br>
<br>
Your Humble Servant<br>
Kaku  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sadad>Sadad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 4:13:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> Your atk is what accuracy is based on. Weapon skill, offense, and strength all increase your atk. If you were to raise your 2hs skill to 90ish you would most likely connect more often.<br>
<br>
Your problem may be that you are trying to hit reds. Mobs that con red are generally harder to hit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 4:23:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> double attack will make you swing more and so hit more..when you get your skill high it makes a huge difference.<br>
<br>
raising your weapon skill will certainly make a difference.<br>
<br>
also you'll hit harder when you hit 20. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urendaelbrigh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rendael Brigh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 4:32:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> I suggest getting a BABS. It swings faster and does more damage. You should be able to get one for 100 to 200p. More swings = more skill ups. <p>Rendael Brigh<BR>
Knight of Truth, 56th shield<BR>
Avengers Federation<BR>
Tholuxe Paells<BR>
Master Smith 210<BR>
Master Brewer 160<BR>
Master Potter 124<BR>
Journeyman Tailor 65<BR>
Master Baker 108<BR>
<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=122156" target="_new">My Magelo character profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 4:47:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> Your attack skill with 2H slashing is still a bit low for your level so yes you will miss a lot with it. If you're grouping most of the time and aren't really called upon to do a lot of damage, then I would continue to practice 2h slashing. Don't worry the higher your skill gets the quicker it will improve.<br>
<br>
When you get double attack at 20, I would suggest going back to 1h slashing. A quicker weapon means more swings, which means more chances to improve double attack. I only put 1 point in double attack last time and it took me 2 or 3 levels to max it. So I'd recommend throwing in about 20 or 30 points, more if you're in a hurry or solo a lot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 409<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 5:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> Roughly your weapon skill in each weapon discipline will go up 5 points each level. The different weapon disciplines are 1h slash, 1h blunt, 2h slash, 2h blunt and piercing. <br>
<br>
Before you weapon skill reaches 100, you only get a word telling you how good your skill is. Average I think is a weapon skill of around 50. Master would be 100. <br>
<br>
Your weapon skill for the 2h sword should be 95 at level 19. You just need to use the 2h weapon more until you become as efficient with it as your level allows. Best to raise the skill in groups or switch to the 2h when the monster is almost dead if the fights are otherwise tight.<br>
<br>
Also before you reach level 20 you are limited to hitting a maximum of 29. Once you reach 20 your maximum damage will go up to somewhere around twice the damage of the weapon which would be 36 in your case.<br>
<br>
My recommendation is to continue using the 2h, switch to 1h when fights get tough and get to level 20. Once you are equally good wielding a 2h sword as you are right now with your 1h sword, then things will be fine =)<br>
<br>
 <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>
60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife<BR>
56 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)<BR>
Dol Amroth
<BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>Typical Raid Setup</a><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66884>AC Solo Gear</a><BR>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ua11e.showPublicProfile?language=EN>A11e</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 6:26:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> I want to thank those of you who took the time to reply.  In addition to the encouragement, I have seen several excellent suggestions.  <br>
<br>
Ironically, I was grouped last night with some higher level players 20- 23 and we were hunting mobs red to me.  While I rarely connected, I noticed that my skill in 2HS did go up more quickly than I had previously when I hunted blues.  Fortunately, my value to the group as a healer far exceeded my meager melee contributions.<br>
<br>
Based upon what I have heard I will:<br>
<br>
1)  Continue using 2HS until I reach 20.<br>
<br>
2)  At 20, I will put the balance of my training points into double attack and switch to using my 1HS and shield until I am close to maxing out double attack.<br>
<br>
3)   When my double attack skill is close to max, I will switch back to my 2HS.  In the meantime, I will keep my eyes open for a better 2HS weapon in my price range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaanya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daanya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 7:37:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> There's really no need to dump points into it, it will level up.<br>
<br>
Only if you solo, really, is it going to matter for dumping points.<br>
<br>
Only time I dumped points was when I started piercing at about 41. Going down to guk w/ a piercing skill of 0 would have meant I hit just about every 25th or 30th swing ;p So I dumped 106 pts into it and never regretted it.<br>
<br>
In your case though, 1 point is enough. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqjonze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqjonze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 7:40:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> Turn the filter on so your misses are filtered out.  Then you will never miss.  I know I don't. <p><b>Jonze</b> 56 Paladin
<br><a href="http://www.eqwhitewind.com"> White Wind on Drinal
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwyrmbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wyrmbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 8:11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res0nwy3/everquest/wyrmbane_sml.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> <br>
Missing is a great frustration and people here answered it quite well.<br>
<br>
Once you hit 20, Just put a single point into Double attack.  That one point will give you a skill of average.    <br>
<br>
Use your sword and shield until Offense, 1hs, and Bash are all maxed (at lvl 20, you should get to 105 in all of them).  At that point put your 2hs back as your main weapon and keep using it.    Your double attack will keep going up, and more importantly, you 2hs will continue to rise.  Yes, it does go up slow, but you will find that around 80 skill or so (good) you will start to see more frequent increases (until about 195ish).<br>
<br>
If you ever solo, make sure to use the 1hs + shield since you will hit more often and live.  But whenever in a group, always use the 2HS.    The other benefit is with 2hs, you should have enough Delay that you can time your stuns to land between swings.   Delay of 1-handers is usually not enough to do that.<br>
<br>
wyrmbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 8:24:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> Nah, don't ever put points into melee stuff.  I was in the same boat as you - I used 1hs until about level 20.  I expected to see greater damage at that point but then realized that my weapon (crystallized blade I think) wasn't even doing enough damage to hit the cap.  <br>
<br>
So then some desperate nutball is selling a BABS in EC for the low low price of 250p (this was back when they went for around 500+).  So I bought it.  My skill was at about... 2.  <br>
<br>
I basically just got into exp groups and if all was going well I'd switch over to the BABS and skill up in it.  It took awhile but I eventually maxed it.  I had to do this all over again when I got a centi warspear later on and had to raise piercing.  <br>
<br>
A lot of people tell me to raise 1hb and 2hb but I think I've seen one weapon in all my time that was even equivalent to the 2hs choices out there.  I know there are some end game weapons that might be worth it but I'm not holding my breath for those.<br>
<br>
Personally, I recommend both the BABS and centi warspear at your level.  The centi warspear is definately the better of the two.  Both of them are dirt cheap and you will max your 2hs and piercing skill.  Piercing is a great skill to raise because many players won't take the time to do so, so a lot of great higher level piercers go for a lot less than they're worth.<br>
<br>
Eventually you should switch to a Mithral 2hs until you can afford a haste item.  The mith 2hs goes for as low as 750.  Realistically this is about as good as it gets until you get a nice haste item, at which point the centi ws is back on top out of the three.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 892<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 9:33:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 100 points of weaponskill</span><hr size=1> Been training up 2h piercing of late.<br>
<br>
With a skill of 100 vs 2hs of 208... ah mist all of 10% more often on tha same beasties. So 100 points of weapon skill seems ter be worth aboot 10% accuracy. Not talking aboot damage rates, just to-hit rates.<br>
 <p>Wulfhere Hausakliufr<BR>
Hammer o Brell, Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utregorfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TregorFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 10:04:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 100 points of weaponskill</span><hr size=1> Hey Kaku,<br>
<br>
I have seen you hunting in unrest as of late.  I think you need to max your 2hs skill and then you will miss alot less.  Trust me.  Double attack at lvl 20 helps alot too.  You either miss more or hit more.  hehe.<br>
<br>
Just get into a group and practice practice practice.  <br>
<br>
Tregor ShieldFist<br>
Gnome Paladin of Brell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulothaniei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LothanieI</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 10:04:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15311.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.chello.at/gemoe/lothfa.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frustrated - Can't hit the broad side of a barn (</span><hr size=1> First of all, Damage is limited in levels 10 and 20. <br>
<br>
Til 10 you will never see a hit above 20. With no weapon. Period<br>
